WHAT IS THIS THING?
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
IFF TO TILES  is a tool that converts tiles drew with  graphics programs to
special  type  of files.  So you can load these files with HIT TILES 2.  To
draw  the  tiles you can use the file EMPTY.pic in directory Pics.  For the
drawing of the tiles you can respect the following NEW RULES:
Now, you can use all the 32 colors, without limitations,  but remember, the
last tree colors are for the pointer



SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
    Any Amiga with some memory and kickstart 1.2 or higher
    Asl.library (optional, only for kickstart 2.0 or higher)
    DiskFont.library
    IconX and Execute commands


BUGS
¯¯¯¯
Don't try to use Asl.library with kickstart below 2.0 (remember, this fact
is valid for all programs)

